President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh to fill the Supreme Court vacancy left by Justice Anthony Kennedy. Judge Kavanaugh has served on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit since 2006 and has authored more than 300 opinions. He has previously worked in the George W. Bush administration and clerked on the Supreme Court for Justice Kennedy. Judge Kavanaugh is known for his legal expertise and ability to persuade and build consensus. He lives in Maryland with his wife and two daughters.